47/*
48 * On some systems, host routes have no need for a netmask.
49 * However DHCP specifies host routes using an all-ones netmask.
50 * This handy function allows easy comparison when the two
51 * differ.
52 */
53static int
54rt_cmp_netmask(const struct rt *rt1, const struct rt *rt2)
55{
56
57 if (rt1->rt_flags & RTF_HOST && rt2->rt_flags & RTF_HOST)
58 return 0;
59 return sa_cmp(&rt1->rt_netmask, &rt2->rt_netmask);
60}
61
62void
63rt_init(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx)
64{
65
66 TAILQ_INIT(&ctx->routes);
67 TAILQ_INIT(&ctx->kroutes);
68 TAILQ_INIT(&ctx->froutes);
69}
70
71static void
72rt_desc(const char *cmd, const struct rt *rt)
73{
74 char dest[INET_MAX_ADDRSTRLEN], gateway[INET_MAX_ADDRSTRLEN];
75 int prefix;
76 const char *ifname;
77 bool gateway_unspec;
78
79 assert(cmd != NULL);
80 assert(rt != NULL);
81
82 sa_addrtop(&rt->rt_dest, dest, sizeof(dest));
83 prefix = sa_toprefix(&rt->rt_netmask);
84 sa_addrtop(&rt->rt_gateway, gateway, sizeof(gateway));
85 gateway_unspec = sa_is_unspecified(&rt->rt_gateway);
86 ifname = rt->rt_ifp == NULL ? "(null)" : rt->rt_ifp->name;
87
88 if (rt->rt_flags & RTF_HOST) {
89 if (gateway_unspec)
90 loginfox("%s: %s host route to %s",
91 ifname, cmd, dest);
92 else
93 loginfox("%s: %s host route to %s via %s",
94 ifname, cmd, dest, gateway);
95 } else if (sa_is_unspecified(&rt->rt_dest) &&
96 sa_is_unspecified(&rt->rt_netmask))
97 {
98 if (gateway_unspec)
99 loginfox("%s: %s default route",
100 ifname, cmd);
101 else
102 loginfox("%s: %s default route via %s",
103 ifname, cmd, gateway);
104 } else if (gateway_unspec)
105 loginfox("%s: %s%s route to %s/%d",
106 ifname, cmd,
107 rt->rt_flags & RTF_REJECT ? " reject" : "",
108 dest, prefix);
109 else
110 loginfox("%s: %s%s route to %s/%d via %s",
111 ifname, cmd,
112 rt->rt_flags & RTF_REJECT ? " reject" : "",
113 dest, prefix, gateway);
114}
115
116void
117rt_headclear0(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx, struct rt_head *rts, int af)
118{
119 struct rt *rt, *rtn;
120
121 if (rts == NULL)
122 return;
123 assert(ctx != NULL);
124 assert(&ctx->froutes != rts);
125
126 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(rt, rts, rt_next, rtn) {
127 if (af != AF_UNSPEC &&
128 rt->rt_dest.sa_family != af &&
129 rt->rt_gateway.sa_family != af)
130 continue;
131 TAILQ_REMOVE(rts, rt, rt_next);
132 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&ctx->froutes, rt, rt_next);
133 }
134}
135
136void
137rt_headclear(struct rt_head *rts, int af)
138{
139 struct rt *rt;
140
141 if (rts == NULL || (rt = TAILQ_FIRST(rts)) == NULL)
142 return;
143 rt_headclear0(rt->rt_ifp->ctx, rts, af);
144}
145
146static void
147rt_headfree(struct rt_head *rts)
148{
149 struct rt *rt;
150
151 while ((rt = TAILQ_FIRST(rts))) {
152 TAILQ_REMOVE(rts, rt, rt_next);
153 free(rt);
154 }
155}
156
157void
158rt_dispose(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx)
159{
160
161 assert(ctx != NULL);
162 rt_headfree(&ctx->routes);
163 rt_headfree(&ctx->kroutes);
164 rt_headfree(&ctx->froutes);
165}
166
167struct rt *
168rt_new0(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx)
169{
170 struct rt *rt;
171
172 assert(ctx != NULL);
173 if ((rt = TAILQ_FIRST(&ctx->froutes)) != NULL)
174 TAILQ_REMOVE(&ctx->froutes, rt, rt_next);
175 else if ((rt = malloc(sizeof(*rt))) == NULL) {
176 logerr(__func__);
177 return NULL;
178 }
179 memset(rt, 0, sizeof(*rt));
180 return rt;
181}
182
183void
184rt_setif(struct rt *rt, struct interface *ifp)
185{
186
187 assert(rt != NULL);
188 assert(ifp != NULL);
189 rt->rt_ifp = ifp;
190#ifdef HAVE_ROUTE_METRIC
191 rt->rt_metric = ifp->metric;
192#endif
193}
194
195struct rt *
196rt_new(struct interface *ifp)
197{
198 struct rt *rt;
199
200 assert(ifp != NULL);
201 if ((rt = rt_new0(ifp->ctx)) == NULL)
202 return NULL;
203 rt_setif(rt, ifp);
204 return rt;
205}
206
207void
208rt_free(struct rt *rt)
209{
210
211 assert(rt != NULL);
212 assert(rt->rt_ifp->ctx != NULL);
213 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&rt->rt_ifp->ctx->froutes, rt, rt_next);
214}
215
216void
217rt_freeif(struct interface *ifp)
218{
219 struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx;
220 struct rt *rt, *rtn;
221
222 if (ifp == NULL)
223 return;
224 ctx = ifp->ctx;
225 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(rt, &ctx->routes, rt_next, rtn) {
226 if (rt->rt_ifp == ifp) {
227 TAILQ_REMOVE(&ctx->routes, rt, rt_next);
228 rt_free(rt);
229 }
230 }
231 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(rt, &ctx->kroutes, rt_next, rtn) {
232 if (rt->rt_ifp == ifp) {
233 TAILQ_REMOVE(&ctx->kroutes, rt, rt_next);
234 rt_free(rt);
235 }
236 }
237}
238
239struct rt *
240rt_find(struct rt_head *rts, const struct rt *f)
241{
242 struct rt *rt;
243
244 assert(rts != NULL);
245 assert(f != NULL);
246 TAILQ_FOREACH(rt, rts, rt_next) {
247 if (sa_cmp(&rt->rt_dest, &f->rt_dest) == 0 &&
248#ifdef HAVE_ROUTE_METRIC
249 (f->rt_ifp == NULL ||
250 rt->rt_ifp->metric == f->rt_ifp->metric) &&
251#endif
252 rt_cmp_netmask(f, rt) == 0)
253 return rt;
254 }
255 return NULL;
256}
257
258static void
259rt_kfree(struct rt *rt)
260{
261 struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx;
262 struct rt *f;
263
264 assert(rt != NULL);
265 ctx = rt->rt_ifp->ctx;
266 if ((f = rt_find(&ctx->kroutes, rt)) != NULL) {
267 TAILQ_REMOVE(&ctx->kroutes, f, rt_next);
268 rt_free(f);
269 }
270}
271
272/* If something other than dhcpcd removes a route,
273 * we need to remove it from our internal table. */
274void
275rt_recvrt(int cmd, const struct rt *rt, pid_t pid)
276{
277 struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx;
278 struct rt *f;
279
280 assert(rt != NULL);
281 ctx = rt->rt_ifp->ctx;
282 f = rt_find(&ctx->kroutes, rt);
283
284 switch(cmd) {
285 case RTM_DELETE:
286 if (f != NULL) {
287 TAILQ_REMOVE(&ctx->kroutes, f, rt_next);
288 rt_free(f);
289 }
290 if ((f = rt_find(&ctx->routes, rt)) != NULL) {
291 char buf[32];
292
293 TAILQ_REMOVE(&ctx->routes, f, rt_next);
294 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "pid %d deleted", pid);
295 rt_desc(buf, f);
296 rt_free(f);
297 }
298 break;
299 case RTM_ADD:
300 if (f != NULL)
301 break;
302 if ((f = rt_new(rt->rt_ifp)) == NULL)
303 break;
304 memcpy(f, rt, sizeof(*f));
305 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&ctx->kroutes, f, rt_next);
306 break;
307 }
308
309#if defined(IPV4LL) && defined(HAVE_ROUTE_METRIC)
310 if (rt->rt_dest.sa_family == AF_INET)
311 ipv4ll_recvrt(cmd, rt);
312#endif
313}
314
315static bool
316rt_add(struct rt *nrt, struct rt *ort)
317{
318 struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx;
319 bool change;
320
321 assert(nrt != NULL);
322 ctx = nrt->rt_ifp->ctx;
323
324 /*
325 * Don't install a gateway if not asked to.
326 * This option is mainly for VPN users who want their VPN to be the
327 * default route.
328 * Because VPN's generally don't care about route management
329 * beyond their own, a longer term solution would be to remove this
330 * and get the VPN to inject the default route into dhcpcd somehow.
331 */
332 if (((nrt->rt_ifp->active &&
333 !(nrt->rt_ifp->options->options & DHCPCD_GATEWAY)) ||
334 (!nrt->rt_ifp->active && !(ctx->options & DHCPCD_GATEWAY))) &&
335 sa_is_unspecified(&nrt->rt_dest) &&
336 sa_is_unspecified(&nrt->rt_netmask))
337 return false;
338
339 rt_desc(ort == NULL ? "adding" : "changing", nrt);
340
341 change = false;
342 if (ort == NULL) {
343 ort = rt_find(&ctx->kroutes, nrt);
344 if (ort != NULL &&
345 ((ort->rt_flags & RTF_REJECT &&
346 nrt->rt_flags & RTF_REJECT) ||
347 (ort->rt_ifp == nrt->rt_ifp &&
348#ifdef HAVE_ROUTE_METRIC
349 ort->rt_metric == nrt->rt_metric &&
350#endif
351 sa_cmp(&ort->rt_gateway, &nrt->rt_gateway) == 0)))
352 {
353 if (ort->rt_mtu == nrt->rt_mtu)
354 return true;
355 change = true;
356 }
357 } else if (ort->rt_dflags & RTDF_FAKE &&
358 !(nrt->rt_dflags & RTDF_FAKE) &&
359 ort->rt_ifp == nrt->rt_ifp &&
360#ifdef HAVE_ROUTE_METRIC
361 ort->rt_metric == nrt->rt_metric &&
362#endif
363 sa_cmp(&ort->rt_dest, &nrt->rt_dest) == 0 &&
364 rt_cmp_netmask(ort, nrt) == 0 &&
365 sa_cmp(&ort->rt_gateway, &nrt->rt_gateway) == 0)
366 {
367 if (ort->rt_mtu == nrt->rt_mtu)
368 return true;
369 change = true;
370 }
371
372#ifdef RTF_CLONING
373 /* BSD can set routes to be cloning routes.
374 * Cloned routes inherit the parent flags.
375 * As such, we need to delete and re-add the route to flush children
376 * to correct the flags. */
377 if (change && ort != NULL && ort->rt_flags & RTF_CLONING)
378 change = false;
379#endif
380
381 if (change) {
382 if (if_route(RTM_CHANGE, nrt) != -1)
383 return true;
384 if (errno != ESRCH)
385 logerr("if_route (CHG)");
386 }
387
388#ifdef HAVE_ROUTE_METRIC
389 /* With route metrics, we can safely add the new route before
390 * deleting the old route. */
391 if (if_route(RTM_ADD, nrt) != -1) {
392 if (ort != NULL) {
393 if (if_route(RTM_DELETE, ort) == -1 && errno != ESRCH)
394 logerr("if_route (DEL)");
395 rt_kfree(ort);
396 }
397 return true;
398 }
399
400 /* If the kernel claims the route exists we need to rip out the
401 * old one first. */
402 if (errno != EEXIST || ort == NULL)
403 goto logerr;
404#endif
405
406 /* No route metrics, we need to delete the old route before
407 * adding the new one. */
408#ifdef ROUTE_PER_GATEWAY
409 errno = 0;
410#endif
411 if (ort != NULL) {
412 if (if_route(RTM_DELETE, ort) == -1 && errno != ESRCH)
413 logerr("if_route (DEL)");
414 else
415 rt_kfree(ort);
416 }
417#ifdef ROUTE_PER_GATEWAY
418 /* The OS allows many routes to the same dest with different gateways.
419 * dhcpcd does not support this yet, so for the time being just keep on
420 * deleting the route until there is an error. */
421 if (ort != NULL && errno == 0) {
422 for (;;) {
423 if (if_route(RTM_DELETE, ort) == -1)
424 break;
425 }
426 }
427#endif
428 if (if_route(RTM_ADD, nrt) != -1)
429 return true;
430#ifdef HAVE_ROUTE_METRIC
431logerr:
432#endif
433 logerr("if_route (ADD)");
434 return false;
435}
436
437static bool
438rt_delete(struct rt *rt)
439{
440 int retval;
441
442 rt_desc("deleting", rt);
443 retval = if_route(RTM_DELETE, rt) == -1 ? false : true;
444 if (!retval && errno != ENOENT && errno != ESRCH)
445 logerr(__func__);
446 /* Remove the route from our kernel table so we can add a
447 * IPv4LL default route if possible. */
448 else
449 rt_kfree(rt);
450 return retval;
451}
452
453static bool
454rt_cmp(const struct rt *r1, const struct rt *r2)
455{
456
457 return (r1->rt_ifp == r2->rt_ifp &&
458#ifdef HAVE_ROUTE_METRIC
459 r1->rt_metric == r2->rt_metric &&
460#endif
461 sa_cmp(&r1->rt_gateway, &r2->rt_gateway) == 0);
462}
463
464static bool
465rt_doroute(struct rt *rt)
466{
467 struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx;
468 struct rt *or;
469
470 ctx = rt->rt_ifp->ctx;
471 /* Do we already manage it? */
472 if ((or = rt_find(&ctx->routes, rt))) {
473 if (rt->rt_dflags & RTDF_FAKE)
474 return true;
475 if (or->rt_dflags & RTDF_FAKE ||
476 !rt_cmp(rt, or) ||
477 (rt->rt_ifa.sa_family != AF_UNSPEC &&
478 sa_cmp(&or->rt_ifa, &rt->rt_ifa) != 0) ||
479 or->rt_mtu != rt->rt_mtu)
480 {
481 if (!rt_add(rt, or))
482 return false;
483 }
484 TAILQ_REMOVE(&ctx->routes, or, rt_next);
485 rt_free(or);
486 } else {
487 if (rt->rt_dflags & RTDF_FAKE) {
488 if ((or = rt_find(&ctx->kroutes, rt)) == NULL)
489 return false;
490 if (!rt_cmp(rt, or))
491 return false;
492 } else {
493 if (!rt_add(rt, NULL))
494 return false;
495 }
496 }
497
498 return true;
499}

501void
502rt_build(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx, int af)
503{
504 struct rt_head routes, added;
505 struct rt *rt, *rtn;
506 unsigned long long o;
507
508 /* We need to have the interfaces in the correct order to ensure
509 * our routes are managed correctly. */
510 if_sortinterfaces(ctx);
511
512 TAILQ_INIT(&routes);
513 TAILQ_INIT(&added);
514
515 switch (af) {
516#ifdef INET
517 case AF_INET:
518 if (!inet_getroutes(ctx, &routes))
519 goto getfail;
520 break;
521#endif
522#ifdef INET6
523 case AF_INET6:
524 if (!inet6_getroutes(ctx, &routes))
525 goto getfail;
526 break;
527#endif
528 }
529
530 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(rt, &routes, rt_next, rtn) {
531 if (rt->rt_dest.sa_family != af &&
532 rt->rt_gateway.sa_family != af)
533 continue;
534 /* Is this route already in our table? */
535 if ((rt_find(&added, rt)) != NULL)
536 continue;
537 if (rt_doroute(rt)) {
538 TAILQ_REMOVE(&routes, rt, rt_next);
539 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&added, rt, rt_next);
540 }
541 }
542
543 /* Remove old routes we used to manage. */
544 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(rt, &ctx->routes, rt_next, rtn) {
545 if (rt->rt_dest.sa_family != af &&
546 rt->rt_gateway.sa_family != af)
547 continue;
548 TAILQ_REMOVE(&ctx->routes, rt, rt_next);
549 if (rt_find(&added, rt) == NULL) {
550 o = rt->rt_ifp->options ?
551 rt->rt_ifp->options->options :
552 ctx->options;
553 if ((o &
554 (DHCPCD_EXITING | DHCPCD_PERSISTENT)) !=
555 (DHCPCD_EXITING | DHCPCD_PERSISTENT))
556 rt_delete(rt);
557 }
558 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&ctx->froutes, rt, rt_next);
559 }
560
561 rt_headclear(&ctx->routes, af);
562 TAILQ_CONCAT(&ctx->routes, &added, rt_next);
563
564getfail:
565 rt_headclear(&routes, AF_UNSPEC);
566}
